headline: TXT Q4 Deep Dive: Management Leans on MV-75 Acceleration and Aviation Execution Amid Cautious Guidance
summary: Aerospace and defense company Textron (NYSE:TXT) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 15.6% year on year to $4.18 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $15.5 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.73 per share was 1.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
